>It is a small fan that fits onto the 3" heater channel that goes from the
>engine to the defrost/heater vents. You cut out a section and clamp this 
>fan
>in and run a switch to the dashboard. It improves the heat flow by about a
>million percent. It blows heat even when you are at an idle.
>
>There is a company that sells a kit advertised in Hot VWs that is not 
>wildly
>overpriced, but it is available at any good boating store. Just ask for a 
>3"
>inline fan.
>
